In England, in the seven days to 09 March, there were 284,123 new confirmed cases (502.4 new cases per 100,000). In the seven days to 02 March, there were 177,794 new cases and so the new cases have risen by 60% (106,329 extra cases). The number of confirmed COVID-19 cases in England so far as at 14 March is 16,644,795 (29,433.7 cases per 100,000 population).
